<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.1//EN"
        "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml11/DTD/xhtml11.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
	<body>

		<h1>Web Application Tools</h1>
		<h2>Content</h2>
		<div class="toc">
			<ul>
				<li>
					<a href="#WARArtifact">Web Application Artifact</a>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
		<h2 id="WARArtifact">Web Application Artifact</h2>
       	<p>
        To create a Web Application (WAR), right click on the CApp project and select <strong>Web Application (WAR)</strong> from the 
        menu. 
        </p>
		<p>
			<br></br>
			<br></br>
			<img alt="New Server Runtime" src="images/war1.png"></img>
			<br></br>
			<br></br>
		</p>
		<p>
		There are two ways to create a Web Application (WAR).  
		</p>
		<ol>
			<li>Web Application (WAR) from Web Project</li>
			<li>Web Application (WAR) in the File System</li>
		</ol>

			<p>With the <strong>Web Application (WAR) from Web Project</strong> option, all the <strong>Dynamic Web Projects</strong> 
			in the workspace will be listed. 
			</p>
			<p>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
				<img alt="New Server Runtime" src="images/war2.png"></img>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
			</p>
			
			<p>Select the project you need and click <strong>Next</strong>.
			</p>
			
			<p>Select the CApp project you want to create <strong>Web Application (WAR)</strong> and click <strong>Finish</strong>.
			</p>
			<p>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
				<img alt="New Server Runtime" src="images/war3.png"></img>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
			</p>	
			
			<p>Now you will see new Web Application (WAR) artifact is created under the selected CApp project.
			</p>
			<p>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
				<img alt="New Server Runtime" src="images/war4.png"></img>
				<br></br>
				<br></br>
			</p>
  		
									
	</body>
</html>
